Description: Fragment of triple-reeded handle of Milesian pottery amphora or oenochoe; white slip; exterior: short horizontal brown dashes down each reed; sides of handle painted
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Museum of Classical Archaeology, Cambridge. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.

Perhaps from a Fikellura style amphora. For parallels, see handle root of British Museum 1924,1201.936. See also Cook, J. M. 'Fikellura Pottery', The Annual of the British School at Athens 34, 1933-1934, pl. 6.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.057)
